<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" />
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      font-size: 14px;
      line-height: 1.5;
    }
    .container {
      max-width: 600px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }
    .header {
      background-color: #002F6C;
      color: white;
      padding: 15px;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .content {
      padding: 20px;
    }
    .footer {
      border-top: 1px solid #dddddd;
      padding-top: 15px;
      font-size: 12px;
      color: #666666;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="header">
      <h1>Maryland Accessible Telecommunications</h1>
    </div>
    
    <div class="content">
      <h2>Disability Certification Form for Patient Needs Updates</h2>
      
      <p>Dear Medical Provider,</p>
      
      <p>We have received the disability certification form for the following patient:</p>
      
      <p>
        <strong>Patient Name:</strong> <%= @constituent.full_name %><br>
        <strong>Application ID:</strong> <%= @application.id %>
      </p>
      
      <p>Unfortunately, the certification form requires the following updates:</p>
      
      <div style="background-color: #f8f8f8; padding: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #002F6C;">
        <%= @rejection_reason %>
      </div>
      
      <h3>Next Steps</h3>
      
      <p>Please submit a revised disability certification form using one of the following methods:</p>
      
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Email:</strong> Reply to this email with the updated certification form attached</li>
        <li><strong>Fax:</strong> Send the updated form to 410-767-4276</li>
      </ol>
      
      <p><strong>Note:</strong> The patient has <%= @remaining_attempts %> remaining submission attempts before they must reapply.</p>
      
      <p>Thank you for your assistance in helping your patient access needed telecommunications services.</p>
      
      <p>
        Sincerely,<br>
        Maryland Accessible Telecommunications Program
      </p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="footer">
      <p>For questions, please contact us at medical-cert@mdmat.org or call 410-767-6960.</p>
      <p>Maryland Accessible Telecommunications (MAT) - Improving lives through accessible communication.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
